    "updated_at": "2023-12-11T15:25:14Z",
    "body": "I had a similar issue on macOS 14.1.2 while using starship 1.16.0.\r\n\r\nUpon investigating, the issue stemmed from missing characters in the prompt. This was resolved by properly setting the `$LOCALE`. It appears to be a conflict between zsh and the prompts.\r\n\r\nadding the locale setting to my zsh environment solves the issue for me:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\necho \"export LANG=en_US.UTF-8\" >> .zshenv\r\n```\r\n\r\nmake sure to restart your shell completely for the changes to take effect.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
